obj_root_law_sections_1:
  sectionId (3978)
  sectionNo (1)
  orderNo 1
  title `Short title, extent and commencement.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_1_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_16_18_00008_198069_1517807325332&sectionId=3978&sectionno=1&orderno=1&orgactid=AC_CEN_16_18_00008_198069_1517807325332
obj_root_law_sections_1_content:
  string
  line `(1) This Act may be called the ^1[Van (Sanrakshan`
  line `Evam Samvardhan) Adhiniyam], 1980.`
  line
  line `(2) It extends to the whole of India ^2***.`
  line
  line `(3) It shall be deemed to have come into force on the 25th day of October, 1980.`
obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by s. 3, ibid., for "Forest (Conservation) Act" (w.e.f. 1-12-2023).`
  line
  line `2. The words "except the State of Jammu and Kashmir" omitted by Act 34 of 2019, s. 95 and the Fifth Schedule`
  line `(w.e.f. 31-10- 2019).`
obj_root_law_sections_1_a:
  sectionId (79953)
  sectionNo 1A
  orderNo 2
  title `Act to cover certain land.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_1_a_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 15 of 2023, s. 4 (w.e.f. 1-12-2023).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_16_18_00008_198069_1517807325332&sectionId=79953&sectionno=1A&orderno=2&orgactid=AC_CEN_16_18_00008_198069_1517807325332
obj_root_law_sections_1_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[1A. Act to cover certain land.--(1) The following land shall be covered under the`
  line `provisions of this Act, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) the land that has been declared or notified as a forest in accordance with the`
  line `provisions of the Indian Forest Act, 1927 (16 of 1927) or under any other law for the time`
  line `being in force;`
  line
  line `(b) the land that is not covered under clause (a), but has been recorded in Government`
  line `record as forest, as on or after the 25th October, 1980:`
  line
  line `Provided that the provisions of this clause shall not apply to such land, which has been`
  line `changed from forest use to use for non-forest purpose on or before the 12th December, 1996 in`
  line `pursuance of an order, issued by any authority authorised by a State Government or an Union`
  line `territory Administration in that behalf.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--For the purposes of this sub-section, the expression "Government record"`
  line `means record held by Revenue Department or Forest Department of the State Government or`
  line `Union territory Administration, or any authority, local body, community or council recognised`
  line `by the State Government or Union territory Administration.`
  line
  line `(2) The following categories of land shall not be covered under the provisions of this Act,`
  line `namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) such forest land situated alongside a rail line or a public road maintained by the`
  line `Government, which provides access to a habitation, or to a rail, and roadside amenity up to a`
  line `maximum size of 0.10 hectare in each case;`
  line
  line `(b) such tree, tree plantation or reafforestation raised on lands that are not specified in`
  line `clause (a) or clause (b) of sub-section (1); and`
  line
  line `(c) such forest land,--`
  line
  line `(i) as is situated within a distance of one hundred kilometres along international`
  line `borders or Line of Control or Line of Actual Control, as the case may be, proposed to be`
  line `used for construction of strategic linear project of national importance and concerning`
  line `national security; or`
  line
  line `(ii) up to ten hectares, proposed to be used for construction of security related`
  line `infrastructure; or`
  line
  line `(iii) as is proposed to be used for construction of defence related project or a camp for`
  line `paramilitary forces or public utility projects, as may be specified by the Central`
  line `Government, the extent of which does not exceed five hectares in a Left Wing Extremism`
  line `affected area as may be notified by the Central Government.`
  line
  line `(3) The exemption provided under sub-section (2) shall be subject to such terms and`
  line `conditions, including the conditions of planting trees to compensate felling of trees undertaken`
  line `on the lands, as the Central Government may, by guidelines, specify.]`
obj_root_law_sections_2:
  sectionId (3979)
  sectionNo (2)
  orderNo 3
  title `Restriction on the dereservation of forests or use of forest land for non-forest purpose.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_2_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_16_18_00008_198069_1517807325332&sectionId=3979&sectionno=2&orderno=3&orgactid=AC_CEN_16_18_00008_198069_1517807325332
obj_root_law_sections_2_content:
  string
  line `^1[(1)]`
  line `Notwithstanding anything contained in any other law for the time being in force in a State, no State`
  line `Government or other authority shall make, except with the prior approval of the Central Government, any`
  line `order directing--`
  line
  line `(i) that any reserved forest (within the meaning of the expression "reserved forest" in any law for`
  line `the time being in force in that State) or any portion thereof, shall cease to be reserved;`
  line
  line `(ii) that any forest land or any portion thereof may be used for any non-forest purpose.`
  line
  line `^2[(iii) that any forest land or any portion thereof may be assigned by way of lease or otherwise to`
  line `any private person or to any authority, corporation, agency or any other organization ^3[subject to`
  line `such terms and conditions, as the Central Government may, by order, specify];`
  line
  line `(iv) that any forest land or any portion thereof may be cleared of trees which have grown`
  line `naturally in that land or portion, for the purpose of using it for reafforestation.]`
  line
  line `^4[Explanation.--For the purposes of this section "non-forest purpose" means the breaking up or`
  line `clearing of any forest land or portion thereof for--`
  line
  line `(a) the cultivation of tea, coffee, spices, rubber, palms, oil-bearing plants, horticultural crops or`
  line `medicinal plants;`
  line
  line `(b) any purpose other than reafforestation,`
  line
  line `^5[but does not include any work relating to or ancillary to conservation, development and`
  line `management of forests and wildlife, such as--`
  line
  line `(i) silvicultural operations including regeneration operations;`
  line
  line `(ii) establishment of check-posts and infrastructure for the front line forest staff;`
  line
  line `(iii) establishment and maintenance of fire lines;`
  line
  line `(iv) wireless communications;`
  line
  line `(v) construction of fencing, boundary marks or pillars, bridges and culverts, check dams,`
  line `waterholes, trenches and pipelines;`
  line
  line `(vi) establishment of zoo and safaris referred to in the Wild Life (Protection) Act, 1972 (53 of`
  line `1972), owned by the Government or any authority, in forest areas other than protected areas;`
  line
  line `(vii) eco-tourism facilities included in the Forest Working Plan or Wildlife Management Plan or`
  line `Tiger Conservation Plan or Working Scheme of that area; and`
  line
  line `(viii) any other like purposes, which the Central Government may, by order, specify.]]`
  line
  line `^1(2) The Central Government may, by order, specify the terms and conditions subject to`
  line `which any survey, such as, reconnaissance, prospecting, investigation or exploration including`
  line `seismic survey, shall not be treated as non-forest purpose.]`
obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Section renumbered as sub-section (1) by Act 15 of 2023, s. 5 (w.e.f. 1-12-2023).`
  line
  line `2. Ins. by Act 69 of 1988, s. 2 (w.e.f. 15-3-1989).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by Act 15 of 2023, s. 5, for "not owned, managed or controlled by Government" (w.e.f. 1-12-2023).`
  line
  line `4. Subs. by Act 69 of 1988, s. 2, for the Explanation (w.e.f. 15-3-1989).`
  line
  line `5. Subs. by Act 15 of 2023, s. 5, for the long line (w.e.f. 1-12-2023).`
  line
  line `6. Ins. by Act 15 of 2023, s. 5 (w.e.f. 1-12-2023)`
obj_root_law_sections_2_a:
  sectionId (57338)
  sectionNo 2A
  orderNo 4
  title `Appeal to National Green Tribunal.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_2_a_content
  footnotes `1.Ins. by Act 19 of 2010, s. 36 and Schedule III (w.e.f. 18-10-2010).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_16_18_00008_198069_1517807325332&sectionId=57338&sectionno=2A&orderno=4&orgactid=AC_CEN_16_18_00008_198069_1517807325332
obj_root_law_sections_2_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[2A. Appeal to National Green Tribunal.—Any person aggrieved, by an order or decision of the`
  line `State Government or other authority made under section 2, on or after the commencement of the National`
  line `Green Tribunal Act, 2010, may file an appeal to the National Green Tribunal established under section 3`
  line `of the National Green Tribunal Act, 2010, in accordance with the provisions of that Act.]`
obj_root_law_sections_3:
  sectionId (3980)
  sectionNo (3)
  orderNo 5
  title `Constitution of Advisory Committee.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_16_18_00008_198069_1517807325332&sectionId=3980&sectionno=3&orderno=5&orgactid=AC_CEN_16_18_00008_198069_1517807325332
obj_root_law_sections_3_content:
  string
  line `The Central Government may constitute a Committee`
  line `consisting of such number of persons as it may deem fit to advise that Government with regard to--`
  line
  line `(i) the grant of approval under section 2; and`
  line
  line `(ii) any other matter connected with the conservation of forests which may be referred to it by the`
  line `Central Government.`
obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_3_a:
  sectionId (55935)
  sectionNo 3A
  orderNo 6
  title `Penalty for contravention of the provisions of the Act.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_a_content
  footnotes `1.Ins. by s. 3, ibid. (w.e.f. 15-3-1989).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_16_18_00008_198069_1517807325332&sectionId=55935&sectionno=3A&orderno=6&orgactid=AC_CEN_16_18_00008_198069_1517807325332
obj_root_law_sections_3_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[3A. Penalty for contravention of the provisions of the Act.--Whoever contravenes or abets the`
  line `contravention or any of the provisions of section 2, shall be punishable with simple imprisonment for a`
  line `period which may extend to fifteen days.]`
obj_root_law_sections_3_b:
  sectionId (55936)
  sectionNo 3B
  orderNo 7
  title `Offences by authorities and Government departments.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_b_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by s. 3, ibid. (w.e.f. 15-3-1989).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_16_18_00008_198069_1517807325332&sectionId=55936&sectionno=3B&orderno=7&orgactid=AC_CEN_16_18_00008_198069_1517807325332
obj_root_law_sections_3_b_content:
  string
  line `^1[3B. Offences by authorities and Government departments.--(1) Where any offence under this Act`
  line `has been committed`
  line
  line `(a) by any department of Government, the head of the department; or`
  line
  line `(b) by any authority, every person who, at the time the offence was committed, was directly in`
  line `charge of, and was responsible to, the authority for the conduct of the business of the authority as well`
  line `as the authority,`
  line
  line `shall be deemed to be guilty of the offence and shall be liable to be proceeded against and punished`
  line `accordingly:`
  line
  line `Provided that nothing contained in this sub-section shall render the head of the department or any`
  line `person referred to in clause (b), liable to any punishment if the proves that the offence was committed`
  line `without his knowledge or that exercised all due diligence to prevent the commission of such offence.`
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section (1), where an offence punishable under the Act`
  line `has been committed by a department of government or any authority referred to in clause (b) of`
  line `sub-section (1) and it is proved that the offence has been committed with the consent or connivance of, or`
  line `is attributable to any neglect on the part, of, any officer, other than the head of the department, or in the`
  line `case of an authority, any person other than the persons referred to in clause (b) of sub-section (1), such`
  line `officer or persons shall also be deemed to be guilty of that offence and shall be liable to be proceeded`
  line `against and punished accordingly.]`
obj_root_law_sections_3_c:
  sectionId (79954)
  sectionNo 3C
  orderNo 8
  title `Power of Central Government to issue directions.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_c_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 15 of 2023, s. 6 (w.e.f. 1-12-2023).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_16_18_00008_198069_1517807325332&sectionId=79954&sectionno=3C&orderno=8&orgactid=AC_CEN_16_18_00008_198069_1517807325332
obj_root_law_sections_3_c_content:
  string
  line `^1[3C. Power of Central Government to issue directions.--The Central Government may,`
  line `from time to time, issue such directions, to any authority under the Central Government, State`
  line `Government or Union territory Administration, or to any organisation, entity or body recognised`
  line `by the Central Government, State Government or Union territory Administration, as may be`
  line `necessary for the implementation of this Act.]`
obj_root_law_sections_4:
  sectionId (3981)
  sectionNo (4)
  orderNo 9
  title `Power to make rules.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_16_18_00008_198069_1517807325332&sectionId=3981&sectionno=4&orderno=9&orgactid=AC_CEN_16_18_00008_198069_1517807325332
obj_root_law_sections_4_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette,`
  line `make rules for carrying out the provisions of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) Every rule made under this Act shall be laid, as soon as may be after it is made, before each House`
  line `of Parliament, while it is in session, for a total period of thirty days which may be comprised in one`
  line `session or in two or more successive sessions, and if, before the expiry of the session immediately`
  line `following the session or the successive sessions aforesaid, both Houses agree in making any modification`
  line `in the rule or both Houses agree that the rule should not be made, the rule shall thereafter have effect only`
  line `in such modified form or be of no effect, as the case may be; so, however, that any such modification or`
  line `annulment shall be without prejudice to the validity of anything previously done under that rule.`
obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_5:
  sectionId (3982)
  sectionNo (5)
  orderNo 10
  title `Repeal and saving.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_16_18_00008_198069_1517807325332&sectionId=3982&sectionno=5&orderno=10&orgactid=AC_CEN_16_18_00008_198069_1517807325332
obj_root_law_sections_5_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Forest (Conservation) Ordinance, 1980 (17 of 1980) is hereby`
  line repealed.
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding such repeal, anything done or any action taken under the provisions of the said`
  line `Ordinance shall be deemed to have been done or taken under the corresponding provisions of this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes:
  string
  line
